# @debugger

**5-phase systematic debugging. Mention @debugger when stuck on a bug.**

## Phases

### 1. REPRODUCE
- Get exact steps to trigger
- Confirm error is consistent
- Note environment details

### 2. ISOLATE
- Binary search: comment out halves
- Find minimal reproduction
- Identify exact line/function

### 3. INSTRUMENT
- Add strategic logging
- Trace data flow
- Capture state at failure point

### 4. ROOT CAUSE
- Ask "why" 5 times
- Find the CAUSE, not the symptom
- Check project-notes/bugs.md for past similar issues

### 5. FIX + PREVENT
- Fix the root cause
- Add test to prevent recurrence
- Log solution to project-notes/bugs.md

## Anti-Patterns

- Guessing without reproducing
- Fixing symptoms, not causes
- Skipping the prevention step
